sentences: Milo Lombardi (born 1988) is an Italian jazz saxophonist and composer.
He graduated from the Rossini Conservatory in 2008 and moved to Sydney, Australia, where he performed with the Sydney Wind Symphony Orchestra.
He returned to Italy in 2009 where he studied composition and jazz arranging with Massimo Morganti.
In 2014 he launched a crowdfunding campaign to support the production and publishing of his debut album, Going Nowhere (Enjoying the Ride).
In 2014 one of his compositions (Circular Quay) received an honorable mention in the jazz category from the International Songwriting Competition of that year.
In 2014 he launched a crowdfunding campaign to support the production and publishing of his debut album, Going Nowhere (Enjoying the Ride).
The campaign was successful and the album was published the same year.
He then moved to Berlin, Germany, where he currently resides.
